# A11y Audit - Cursor Rules

## Project
Accessibility audit framework using Playwright + axe-core + 22 custom WCAG 2.0/2.1/2.2 checks.

## Tech Stack
- TypeScript (strict mode)
- Playwright Test as the runner
- @axe-core/playwright for baseline
- Custom checks in `utils/accessibility-audit.ts`
- JSON-based trend tracking

## Code Style
- Use `@playwright/test` imports, never raw playwright
- Prefer `page.evaluate()` for DOM inspection over locator chains
- Use the AccessibilityAudit class for all checks
- CSS selectors generated inside page.evaluate, not from Node side
- Violations use the A11yViolation interface with: rule, impact, description, wcagCriteria, elements, selectors, howToFix

## Locator Priority (for identifying elements)
1. getByRole()
2. getByLabel()
3. getByTestId()
4. locator() with CSS (last resort)

## File Layout
- `tests/` — specs (deep-accessibility, site-crawl, ci-audit, w3c-demo-audit)
- `utils/` — core engine, contrast-ratio, site-crawler, trend-tracker
- `fixtures/` — Playwright fixtures (a11y.fixture.ts)
- `scripts/` — CLI utilities
- `.github/workflows/` — GitHub Actions CI

## Key Patterns
- All custom checks are private methods on AccessibilityAudit class
- runFullAudit() orchestrates axe-core + all custom checks
- SiteCrawler discovers pages via sitemap + link-following, then calls AccessibilityAudit per page
- TrendTracker persists results as JSON and generates markdown/HTML reports
- Contrast ratio uses WCAG relative luminance (sRGB linearization → L calculation → ratio formula)

## Don't
- Don't add external dependencies without asking
- Don't modify the A11yViolation interface without updating all consumers
- Don't use heuristics for contrast — use the actual formula in contrast-ratio.ts
